Citation.sTitle: Isobaric vapor-liquid equilibria for binary and ternary mixtures with cyclohexane, cyclohexene, and morpholine at 100 kPa
Citation.sAbstract: Vapor-liquid equilibria (VLE) data at 100 kPa have been determinated for the ternary system cyclohexane + cyclohexene + morpholine and two constituent binary systems cyclohexane + morpholine and cyclohexene + morpholine. The thermodynamic consistency of experimental data has been verified. Both binary systems deviate moderately from ideality without the presence of an azeotrope. The VLE data have been well correlated using local composition models (Wilson, NRTL and UNIQUAC) and have been also predicted with the original UNIFAC.
